What are key fewtures of Python?

Python is a high-level, interpreted, and object-oriented programming language. It is dynamically typed, which allows faster development. It has a simple and readable syntax, making it easy to learn and maintain. Python is platform-independent, so it can run on different operating systems. It also provides automatic memory management through garbage collection. Additionally, it has a large standard library and a rich ecosystem of third-party libraries


why python is dynamically typed?
A dynamically typed language is one where you don’t need to declare the data type of a variable explicitly. The type is determined automatically at runtime based on the value assigned. This makes coding faster and more flexible, but it can also lead to more runtime errors if types are misused.

